history.content:
You should have had a final appointment with an advisor last semester. 

Are you on the degree list for this semester? You can check in tele bears, but if not you need to add yourself.

To add yourself, there's also a button in tele bears.

Other that I don't think there's much to do. **

** Caveats:

Things to do still include passing classes and pay tuition.

Yes, you will still want to do one last degree check with your ESS advisor. This is the person who ultimately clears you for graduation so it's good to just make sure you're on the same page. 

In terms of engineering's commencement, online registration will begin on Wednesday, February 11th. I believe you'll receive an email from the Dean's Office with more info. 

- Olivia

children.subject: ESS also has Wednesday drop-in sessions. You may try to go to one of them if you don't want to wait until 23rd.

Since you are my student I have already checked your classes and have emailed you confirmation to your Berkeley email address.

Drop-in hours are until 3:30 pm today.  Generally drop-in is on Wednesdays from 9-11:30 am and 1-3:30 pm unless your ESS advisor is in a meeting. 

Students should be checking their requirements now in case they need to make adjustments to their schedules.  The last day to add/drop classes is Friday, February 20 but there are fees associated with adding and/or dropping at this time.

I've just made an appointment for ESS advising on 2/23.

Thank you for your help!
